
test_tmc: Demonstrate the usage of TMC API to get random bytes

To run (load and start) container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_tmc.img

Usage: {command} {size} [CONFIG] [CONTROL]

command: tmc-set-config
         tmc-generate
         tmc-instantiate
         tmc-reseed-generate
         tmc-uninstantiate
         tmc-reseed
         tmc-health-check
         tmc-close

tmc-set-config: command used to set TMC Configuration with provided config
and control values
Default TMC configuration values are used if configuration is not set
CONFIG     : EIP-76 Config initialization value (optional)
CONTROL    : EIP-76 Control initialization value (optional)

size       : Requested random data size in bytes

To set with default TMC configuration
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-set-config
Default values are: Control=0x400 config=0xc000102

To set with known TMC configuration
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-set-config {CONFIG} {CONTROL}
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-set-config 0xc000102 0x400

To generate random data of 30 bytes
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-generate 30
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-reseed-generate 24
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-reseed 32
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-generate 10
$ cmtest cmd -f100 tmc-health-check 32

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
